**Myndshift Group** supports a number of industries including mining,
civil construction and heavy engineering.  With our extensive experience
and wide-reaching network, we are proud to deliver the highest quality
project personnel in partnership with some of Australia's largest
companies.\
  \
Myndshift Group have been engaged by our client partner a well renowned
contract miner to recruit a **Production Superintendent **for their
large open-cut coal project in the Darling Downs region.\
\
**About the Role:\
**\
Our client is a well-established and growing mining contractor
delivering safe, efficient, and high-quality services across major
mining coal operations. Due to continued growth, they are seeking an
experienced **Production Superintendent** to lead site-based operations
and drive performance across people, plant, and production.\
\
Reporting to the Project Manager, you will play a critical leadership
role in ensuring production targets are met while maintaining the
highest standards of safety, cost control, and operational discipline.\
\
**Key Responsibilities:**

-   Lead and mentor Supervisors and frontline teams to achieve
    production and safety targets

-   Oversee daily and weekly production planning and execution

-   Drive a strong safety culture aligned with client and company
    standards

-   Manage equipment utilisation, availability, and productivity

-   Monitor costs, budgets, and operational KPIs

-   Build effective working relationships with clients and internal
    stakeholders

-   Ensure compliance with site procedures, statutory requirements, and
    company systems

-   Support continuous improvement initiatives across mining operations

**About You:**

-   Proven experience in a Production Superintendent role

-   Strong background in open pit mining within a contracting
    environment

-   Demonstrated leadership capability with a hands-on, proactive
    approach

-   Solid understanding of production planning, cost control, and fleet
    management

-   Excellent communication and stakeholder engagement skills

-   Commitment to safety leadership and continuous improvement

-   Relevant statutory qualifications (or ability to obtain)

**What's on Offer:**

-   Competitive salary package aligned with experience

-   8/6 roster providing excellent work-life balance

-   DIDO or local accommodation options available

-   Opportunity to work with a reputable and growing mining contractor

-   Long-term role with strong job security and career development
    opportunities

If you\'re an experienced Production Superintendent looking for your
next opportunity, we'd love to hear from you. Click **Apply Now** to
submit your resume or contact us confidentially to find out more.\
